{
  "title": "Using <span class=\"vgi-logo\">Vulnogram</span> with CVE Services",
  "outputMarkdown": "index.md",
  "screenshotsDir": "screenshots",
  "hero": {
    "src": "https://vulnogram.org/css/Vulnogram-og.jpg",
    "alt": "Vulnogram - Reserve, Manage, Publish CVEs.",
    "href": "https://www.vulnogram.org/",
    "caption": "Vulnogram - Reserve, Manage, Publish CVEs."
  },
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "access",
      "title": "1. Access <span class=\"vgi-logo\">Vulnogram</span>",
      "text": "Open [Vulnogram.org](https://www.vulnogram.org) for a quick start. The instance on [Vulnogram.org](https://www.vulnogram.org) enables CNAs to use the browser to draft, manage, and publish CVE records. To enable multiple CNA team members to collaborate on drafts in a cental place, download and set up Vulnogram in [Team server mode](https://github.com/Vulnogram/Vulnogram?tab=readme-ov-file#vulnogram-team-deployment)."
    },
    {
      "id": "login",
      "title": "2. Login to CVE Services",
      "text": "Open the **CVE Portal** panel, select the target portal (`production`, `test`, `adp-test`, or local), and authenticate with your CNA short name, CVE user, and API key."
    },
    {
      "id": "reserve",
      "title": "3. Reserve CVE IDs",
      "text": "After login, use **Reserve One CVE** or the dropdown batch actions to reserve IDs for the current year, next year, or previous year. Use state/year filters to find reserved IDs."
    },
    {
      "id": "details",
      "title": "4. Enter CVE Record Details",
      "text": "Use the **Editor** tab to enter vulnerability details, affected products, references, and metrics. Switch between **Editor**, **Source**, and **Preview** tabs while drafting.\n\nFor repeated CNA or ADP work, open the **Configure Default Settings** dialog from the top-right settings button <span class=\"rbtn vgi-cog\"></span>. It lets you simplify the form for new entries by choosing default set of fields to show and by setting default vendor, product, and version-type values, which helps reduce repetitive edits and keeps new records more consistent."
    },
    {
      "id": "publish",
      "title": "5. Publish to CVE Services",
      "text": "Use **Publish CVE** to submit the record to the currently selected portal. In test mode, publishing targets the CVE Services test environment."
    },
    {
      "id": "admin",
      "title": "6. Manage Users and API Keys (Admin)",
      "text": "Organization administrators can open **Users** in the portal view to add users, update profile and role attributes, disable accounts, and reset API secrets."
    },
    {
      "id": "reject",
      "title": "7. How to Reject a CVE ID",
      "text": "Use **Reject this CVE ID** and **Reject this ID** controls to retire unused IDs or withdraw published records. The two workflows below show where each reject action lives."
    }
  ],
